{
  "stem": "142.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Kojak was one of the Kapos of Crematorium II.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we were only left, now, 100 of us, and-- and 26 Greeks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And January-- January 15, when the Russians were coming, the-- on January 18, the Birkenau-- Auschwitz and Birkenau-- the Birkenau actually was evacuated.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were on that Block 13.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Germans were mixed up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They didn't know what they were doing, so we came out of that Block 13, and we got together with all the camp, the thousands of people, and start marching.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They put us to march from Birkenau to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That took quite a few hours, about three miles, two and a half miles.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know who I was with.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was 20-20 marching.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was alone. 20-20 marching.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think my brother and Danny was together, but I was with other people, 20-20 marching.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We march to Auschwitz, and from there, after stopping a few hours, we start walking for days.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Two, three days walking.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember then very perfectly was the-- the 18th of January, 1945, and outside was 23 below zero.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the only thing that I can tell you today is that I survived by closing my eyes and saying, how beautiful Athens with the sunshine.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And repeating that, many times, I start sweating.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Believe me, I am telling you now.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I had a blanket, and I threw it out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we marched, and we marched for days until we arrive to a railroad station, where they put us in open wagons, there-- 150 in each one.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we-- after a day or so, we arrive at Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Marching thousands of people.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And whoever couldn't march, the-- the army, the SS, was behind us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would kill anyone that they couldn't make it.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
